FBIS3-35393 "drnes037_n_94005" FBIS-NES-94-037 Document Type:Daily Report 24 Feb 1994 LEBANON Hizballah Leader Criticizes Government Policy NC2402085994 Beirut Voice of Lebanon in Arabic 0615 GMT 24 Feb 94 NC2402085994 Beirut Voice of Lebanon Language: Arabic Article Type:BFN [Text] Hizballah Secretary General Hasan Nasrallah has said that Prime Minister Rafiq al-Hariri's government was established according to the settlement plan of capitulation in the area. He noted that the government's projects are inspired by peace with Israel. He accused some state officials of seeking to cause a clash between Hizballah and the Lebanese Army over implementation of commitments, which he said the government gave to the U.S. secretary of state.
